The AZ ECG Centre, in the Cardiovascular Safety Center of Excellence and SKGs (CVS CoE and SKGs) in Global Patient Safety, is AstraZeneca´s ECG Core Laboratory. We deliver scientific/medical advice and ECG services across therapeutic areas. We strive toward scientific, technical and operational excellence in ECG study design, analysis and interpretation using state-of-the-art, in-house developed tools.
We are now looking for a Consultant EClysis Project Resource- UAT Test Coordinator (ECG Technical Advisor) to join our team in Gothenburg, Sweden.

The position
Envirotainer was founded in 1985 and currently has a fleet of more than 6,000 active airfreight containers that ensure that temperature-sensitive pharmaceuticals can be delivered from where they are produced to the patient safely. Every day, millions of doses of pharmaceuticals from all types of pharmaceutical manufacturers worldwide are successfully shipped in their containers. Due to continued strong growth, we are now looking for a BI & Data Analytics Manager to join the Envirotainer IT Architecture & Data Analytics team.
Your primary focus will be to manage the BI & Data Analytics domain from an IT perspective. This includes managing and developing new and existing data platforms and tools that provides the business with data, tools, and capabilities to analyze data and produce business reports, dashboards, and analytical insights needed for data driven decisions and formal reporting.

Life at Winningtemp

Winningtemp offers the market an unique and revolutionary technology for creating successful work places. This is done by collecting and visualizing real-time data that describes the employee's experience of leadership, meaningfulness, control and joy at work.
Today, Winningtemp consists of a wonderful and ambitious group of 115+ people in the offices in Gothenburg, Stockholm, Oslo and London. The head quarter is newly renovated (of course with a lot of purple ) in the middle of central Gothenburg.

At Winningtemp we care about the well-being of our employees and therefore we of course work continuously with our own tool to be an attractive employer. We have grown by over 2100% in recent years and we continue to grow.
By 2024, our goal is to make an impact on more than 4 million people through our product.

So what is the role about?

As a Data Engineer at Winningtemp, you will work with many different internal stake holders, with a focus on maintaining data, creating data tools and improving internal processes within your area.
Your mission is to ensure that our data generates actionable and valuable results for the business, and ultimately our customers. You will have an important role linked to an important mission of ours; to become One Winningtemp throughout the whole organization.

Other areas of responsibilities;

Your team and manager ‍ ‍ ‍

In this role you will work close to our senior Data scientist, Miroslav, someone you will have daily communication with. Miroslav has two PhDs, including one in artificial intelligence from Stockholm University. He has eight years of experience in academia - during which his research was funded by some of the most prestigious fellowships available, including the Marie-Sklodowska Currie Fellowship. Miroslav works in Stockholm, but this position is also available in Gothenburg.

Miroslav is a very appreciated colleague, dedicated and eager to share his knowledge and experience in the field, everything to make you learn as much as possible.
In this role, you will also be working close to all our different departments, meaning you will have collaboration over the whole organization.

You will be reporting to our CFO and be a part of his team. The CFO is situated in Gothenburg.

Are you the one we are looking for?

Winningtemp is the place where we all succeed together, something that you also feel is essential in your daily work, teamwork makes the dreamwork. You are therefor a team player and enjoy sharing ideas and learnings with the people around you.

You appreciate to plan your work well, and always complete what you've started. You set high goals for yourself, and always does what it takes to achieve good results. In addition to that, you look outside the box to think in new ways, meaning you are good at finding solutions to problems that arise. You are up-to-date in your area of expertise, and you have a great interest in always learning more about new techniques and systems within your area.

You have 4+ years of experience in a Data Engineer role, and you have a degree, or its equivalent, in Computer Science, Statistics, Informatics, Information Systemor similar. You haveadvanced SQL knowledge and experience working with relational databases, query authoring (SQL) as well as working familiarity with a variety of databases. You have beenbuilding and optimizing ‘big data’ data pipelines, architectures, and data sets. You have been working with structured and unstructured datasets, and you are used to build processes supporting data transformation, data structures, metadata, dependency, and workload management. You have successfully manipulated, processed, and extracted value from large disconnected datasets.

You have experience in using one and/or several following software and tools:


No worries if you do not experience in all of the areas and/or tools, we will guide you along the way!

What's in it for me?

Why Winningtemp?

As an employee at Winningtemp, you will be part of our purple family

With us, you will find energetic and loyal colleagues who help each other succeed together. With us, everyone is equally valuable, regardless of gender, ethnicity and background. Diversity is also something we work actively with and something we value. We share happiness every day, not only for our product and the work we do, but also for each other. The commitment of each employee is what really makes us stand out from other companies. You can expect a supportive workplace where everyone works together towards our vision; to forever change how people succeed together!

We promise you; you will be impressed!

Personality and logical test - > Interview with recruiter - > Interview with the future manager - > Interview with closest colleague - > Reference check - > Offer

We handle applications continuously so don't hesitate to apply as soon as possible!

Description:
Coody is changing the consulting industry with a new model designed to benefit the individual, not the consulting company. We do this by combining the benefits of being a freelancer with the security of a traditional employment.

This means that we pay the best salary in the industry, provide fantastic benefits while at the same time being a secure workplace with a fixed monthly salary, stable employment terms and above all - a wonderful community and really good exchange of knowledge.

Why chose when you can have both?

We have simply stripped away all unnecessary overhead between yourself and the company to be able to offer you a platform that will help you achieve your priorities in life and at the same time work on meaningful projects for some of the country's most exciting digital leaders.

(We do work for companies such as Spotify, Mathem, Hemnet, Bokio, Polestar, Tobii and others).

WE ARE HIRING DATA ENGINEERS TO BE PART OF CHANGING THE WORLD OF CONSULTING TOGETHER WITH COODY AND OUR CLIENTS!

What we look for

We are looking for data engineer to work together with our exciting clients who are leading products companies, startups and scaleups. You’ll work as an integral part of our clients team to solve complex technical challenges in modern cloud environments.

In addition to this, you are interested in handling larger amounts of data and have worked as a Data Engineer or a similar role before where development has been in focus. When working as a consultant with Coody it’s crucial that you are communicative and can work well with others.

Your background

What we offer

We offer you an opportunity to work with exciting challenges and projects in modern cloud environments where you will work with developers and data scientists.

At your service is an experienced sales-team with best-in-industry tools and the right network to find you the perfect assignment and give you the best time of your career!

You will focus on working on longer assignments for between 6 months to 3 years, that will both challenge your knowledge and give you the best possible use of your skill set. You will work as an integral part of the client’s organization, remote or on-site. We do not work with customers in morally dubious industries.

We have a limit on quarterly hires - so don’t wait. Send us your application and get in contact with us in a blink of an eye!

In a world where product size labels are unreliable, Volumental is the footwear industry's leading FitTech™ company, using 3D scans and a one-of-a-kind, AI-powered recommendation engine to match everyone with the shoes that fit them best.

With top brand and retail partners across the world including New Balance, Bauer, The Athlete's Foot, Ecco and XXL, our footprint spans 2500+ stores across 46 countries, and counting.

Volumental’s data and machine learning platforms power all our products, communicate with 3000+ devices spread across six continents, and serve 18 million users - quickly growing. This brings in a large variation of data modalities including, 10s of millions of 3D scans, purchases, inventory, product catalog data, user interactions, and many more. To make this data useful and easy to work with, it is organized, indexed, and served in the different formats that satisfy the needs of our different products that build on top of it.

We are now looking for a data engineer to help us expand our analytics products - ensuring they have access to all the multi-modal data they require to provide an engaging, reliable, and fast experience.

Description:
ABOUT NORMATIVE

At Normative we are creating the norm for carbon accounting by providing intelligence to companies to reduce their climate footprint. We translate financial data into tangible carbon insights enabling companies to understand and reduce their carbon emission. What we do has a real and positive impact on the climate - and you can be a part of this too!

THE ROLE
We are looking for a passionate and curious Sustainability Engineer to join our growing engineering team. As a Sustainability Engineer, you will be key to ensuring the scientific integrity of Normative and you’ll be building the data foundation of our products. Our goal is to provide our customers with precise and scientifically sound estimates of carbon emissions, and every improvement you make to this process directly contributes to helping companies reach net zero emissions.

WHAT YOU WILL DO
WE THINK YOU WILL BE A GOOD MATCH IF
THE TEAM


We also believe you enjoy working in an environment with typical challenges of a growing company, asking a lot of questions and learning new things. At Normative we believe that collaboration with teammates is essential and you’ll thrive if you like to explain and discuss technical approaches with other engineers.

LOCATION
Normative operates on a hybrid remote model with a main office in Stockholm. For this role you can be based either in Stockholm or work remotely within Sweden.

When hired remotely within Sweden, we will offer you a home office set up and you will be expected to travel to Stockholm to meet your team/the company approximately 6 times per year (depending on role). To ensure we practice what we preach we use trains for trips under 6 hours of travel and flights only for longer travels.

THE PROCESS
We adopt a continuous selection process, so make sure to apply with your CV and portfolio as soon as possible! Normative handles sensitive financial data and we will therefore conduct a background check before signing any candidate.

Zebware understand that data is a critical component of any business, and that using it effectively can be a complex, slow and costly task. At Eppow, we’re passionate about solving complex engineering problems which have actual societal value.

What does that mean? These past years the focus has been the patient journey which is great but one very vital aspect has been forgotten. What about the doctors and nurses? We all expect to meet a doctor or a nurse at a hospital, not an empty chair. Here is where Eppow comes in - we empower hospitals, clinics and healthcare professionals to find, contact and contract each other unrestrictedly.

We are a diverse and growing team with our headquarters in Norrsken House, Stockholm. Together we are leading the development of the healthcare industry and are now looking for a savvy developer that wants to help us evolve the platform.

ABOUT TECH AT EPPOW
As a Software Engineer you will be a vital part of our tech team, meaning you will have the mandate and influence over how we develop the platform and structure our tech stack. As we grow into our costume, we now need to re-envision our core architecture. Some of the underlying questions that are driving this change are:

ABOUT THE ROLE
Our current tech stack is based on Java for the backend and standard web for the frontend. However, we are naturally very open to new ideas considering the challenges we are facing. So, any experience you might bring from other technologies is welcomed.


You like to be given much freedom and appreciate having the responsibility that comes with that. You are not afraid to develop new solutions, and you think it's educational to fail. You keep up to date with new technologies, and you are used to adopting new technologies. You are curious and would love to further develop your skills.


Do you want to be a part of revolutionizing the healthcare industry and be a part of the solution? Join as our Dev team and help us evolve our platform and let’s have fun whilst doing it!

Alexis - the helper of People

Alexis is an HR platform founded in Sweden by tech and HR entrepreneurs and used by some of the best scale-ups in Europe today! Alexis is changing the way small and medium businesses handle their people processes and people administration by making it effortless, simple and fast. In this way, we enable companies to create a better workplace and an exceptional employee experience. Our vision is to become the most loved people platform by employees.

⭐️ About the role

As a Senior Fullstack Engineer at Alexis, you will join our team of developers as a key contributor in building a world-class product that our customers will love using. You will be using the latest and greatest technologies to develop new features, continuously improve our product from both a backend and frontend/UX/UI point of view, as well as leverage advanced algorithms, AI and ML, in order to build an innovative platform.

The tech stack for this role includes

What you’ll be doing

Your qualifications

To succeed in this role we believe you are an advocate for a communicative culture that empowers cross-functional teamwork. You take initiative to drive the work forward and use your technical expertise combined with a problem solving approach to identify potential improvements that allow us to scale our products and features successfully.

What we offer

At Alexis, an inclusive and open-minded workplace awaits you. We promise you a high level of autonomy, fantastic people, and many development opportunities. We believe in our people and focus on development and results rather than control. We share common beliefs to create a trusting, collaborative and learning culture. We are all about flexibility, whether you want to work from your couch at home or sit with your colleagues in our offices located in Stockholm and Karlstad.

The hiring process

The hiring process is a two-way street. It's as important for you to get to know us better as it is for us to get to know you. We are building a diverse team where our skills complement and balance each other and our hiring process typically includes coding and psychometric testing early on to assess your relevant skills as fairly and objectively as possible. Let us know if you are interested and apply directly with your phone, without a resume, if you'd like. You can provide a link to your LinkedIn page or similar.

We look forward to hearing from you!

Job_title: System Engineer within Energy Storage System at Electromobility
Description:
Take the opportunity to join the exciting change journey Electromobility is embarking, when creating the future electric powertrains for our customers as well as the future working place to nurture innovation. Electromobility is one of the main development areas within Volvo Group Truck and was created to be in the forefront of electrified transport solutions for a more sustainable tomorrow.
Are you a System engineer with an analytic mindset and a passion for working with quality in the state-of-the art battery development area? Join us now!

This is us, your new colleagues at Electromobility
We are responsible for the transition from conventional powertrains to electromobility and to secure a stepwise implementation in different segments/regions. We develop and drive the electromobility product portfolio for Trucks and Buses as well as creating opportunities for all business areas within Volvo Group. Electromobility is a growing agile driven organization in place to shape the future!
The importance of electromobility is growing every day and a key component within the electrified powertrain is the Energy Storage System (ESS). We are accountable for the lifecycle management of the Energy Storage System, from advanced engineering, throughout product development into the maintenance phase.
You will be part of an agile and approachable organization with skilled product teams consisting of passionate people. We work in an optimistic atmosphere, where joy, knowledge sharing, and openness are key characteristics, working with tasks you cannot imagine today.


You will be part of the Product management team for Medium Range Energy Storage Systems as part of the product development area. We are expanding and are recruiting a System engineer with a customer-centric approach responsible for product and field quality. You will have an important role for the quality of the products and understanding how the battery systems are applied by our customers. You will be involved in technical decisions towards projects and suppliers, making sure that we continuously improve the quality.


We believe that to be successful in this position, you will have the System engineering view on quality for trucks that are in production and aftermarket, always with the customer in focus. You need a good understanding of the applications and how the battery packs are used and applied. You have an analytic- mindset and putting pride in delivering high quality products and solutions. Confident in leading system solution towards suppliers and product teams. We also believe that you feel comfortable of owning and taking responsibility of your system and quality and do so with great attitude.

Who are you?

Description:
We at Centiglobe are looking for a Senior Backend Engineer that loves developing high-quality code. Centiglobe creates a collaborative ecosystem that delivers frictionless instant payments in a multi-currency environment. The platform offers a decentralized, global solution that eliminates the need of the many intermediaries in the financial system. This gives banks, financial institutions and businesses the possibility to send and receive payments globally, done instantly and directly between each other at a fraction of the cost compared to current solutions. We leverage new technology, a blockchain-based decentralized exchange architecture, to modernize the process of transferring value. Centiglobe believes in a collaborative, efficient and sustainable global payments ecosystem.

The position

Description:
Alexis - the helper of People

Alexis is an HR platform founded in Sweden by tech and HR entrepreneurs and used by some of the best scale-ups in Europe today! Alexis is changing the way small and medium businesses handle their people processes and people administration by making it effortless, simple and fast. In this way, we enable companies to create a better workplace and an exceptional employee experience. Our vision is to become the most loved people platform by employees.

⭐️ About the role

As a Fullstack engineer at Alexis, you will play an important role in building a world-class product that our customers will love using. You will be using the latest and greatest technologies to develop new features, continuously improve our product from both a backend and frontend/UX/UI point of view, as well as leverage advanced algorithms, AI and ML, in order to build an innovative platform.

The tech stack for this role includes

What you’ll be doing

Your qualifications

To succeed in this role we believe you want to be an advocate for a communicative culture that empowers cross-functional teamwork. You take initiative to drive the work forward and use your problem solving approach to identify potential improvements that allow us to scale our products and features successfully. We consider it meritable if you have previous experience in TDD and integration testing.

What we offer

At Alexis, an inclusive and open-minded workplace awaits you. We promise you a high level of autonomy, fantastic people, and many development opportunities. We believe in our people and focus on development and results rather than control. We share common beliefs to create a trusting, collaborative and learning culture. We are all about flexibility, whether you want to work from your couch at home or sit with your colleagues in our offices located in Stockholm and Karlstad.

We offer the latest technology equipment, a competitive salary, pension, flexible work hours and locations*, wellness and health benefits, and other nice things. But most importantly, let us grow together!

The hiring process

The hiring process is a two-way street. It's as important for you to get to know us better as it is for us to get to know you. We are building a diverse team whose skills complement and balance each other and our hiring process typically includes coding and psychometric testing early on to assess your relevant skills as fairly and objectively as possible. We also conduct two in-depth interviews for a deeper understanding of your skills as well as to allow you to get the information you need about your potential future workplace.

Let us know if you are interested and apply directly with your phone, without a resume, if you'd like. You can provide a link to your LinkedIn page or similar.

We look forward to hearing from you!

About Validio

Validio is the next generation data quality and reliability company. Our next generation data quality platform monitors and validates both data in motion and data at rest across organizations data pipelines. Validio’s mission is to eliminate bad data and enable organizations to be data-driven with confidence. From startups to multi-billion dollar unicorns, Validio is used by data leaders of all sizes. We believe that you shouldn’t have to be an AirBnB, Uber or Netflix in order to have advanced ML-based data quality technology in place. We also believe that modern data teams and data engineers get better ROI by spending their time on other business-critical tasks rather than building and maintaining their own data quality infrastructure.

Here you will work with a senior team of data and engineering professionals with backgrounds from renowned research institutions, leading startups, and established tech companies. Named as one of the hottest start-ups in Stockholm by publications such as Wired, we are gearing up for expansion, and now you can be part of our journey!

About the role

Validio is on an exciting growth journey and this is a rare opportunity to be a founding team member and leader of the Customer Success team in a very purpose-driven organization. This is a great opportunity to help shape the future of the data industry and its real-world impact.

Validio is looking for someone to build and lead our Customer Success function from the ground up, meaning ownership of customer satisfaction and success, as well increasing the product adoption among existing customers. At Validio we work on some of the most exciting modern data infrastructure architectures and our customers challenge us with interesting new data quality validation and monitoring requirements continuously. As the complexity grows for both us and our customers, we are looking to our Customer Success Lead to strategize and lead customers to solutions. This is done with clear data requirement mapping, use case discovery, Validio evangelism, and oftentimes educating users about our product.

As our Customer Success Lead, you will manage our customer relationships, become a trusted advisor to our users, and contribute to Validio’s fast-growing success. You will be the voice of the user and collaborate closely with product and engineering to make sure key improvements are added to the roadmap. You must be able to capture and contextualize product feedback for our engineering and product teams, track issue resolutions, explain new feature enhancements, and mitigate/prioritize any pain points before they become critical issues.

What you’ll do

We believe you have


Here at Validio we offer you the chance to be part of something truly amazing and with a world class team, there is no limit to what we can achieve together. We promise that you will be challenged, pushed to develop your skill set and get the opportunity to work alongside amazing and smart colleagues from all over the world on our mission to eliminate bad data.

For now begin your journey with us by clicking "Apply" below. We cannot wait to meet you!

Are you a skilled Data Engineer and like working in agile cross functional teams? Are you creative and communicative by default? Do you have an interest in automating processes? Then this might be the role for you!
About Avinode
“Avinode was created back in 2002 to answer a straightforward problem: operators had empty planes and brokers had clients that wanted to fly. And yet there was no real-time online marketplace where these two groups could explore and buy each other’s services. Avinode revolutionized the industry by bringing it online. It is now the go-to platform to buy and sell charter online. Every year, Avinode processes around 4.5 million trip searches and 6 million trip requests. We are also at the technological forefront of the shift to the online booking of private air charter. The web apps and APIs implemented by our customers see around 2 million searches per year – and growing.” – Avinode

About the position
Do you have a passion for Science and Innovation? Would you like to apply your expertise in testing and implementing cardiac digital systems and tools? Then this might be the right position for you!
The AZ ECG Centre, in the Cardiovascular Safety Center of Excellence and SKGs (CVS CoE and SKGs) in Global Patient Safety, is AstraZeneca´s ECG Core Laboratory. We deliver scientific/medical advice and ECG services across therapeutic areas. We strive toward scientific, technical and operational excellence in ECG study design, analysis and interpretation using state-of-the-art, in-house developed tools.
We are now looking for a Consultant EClysis Project Resource- UAT Test Coordinator (ECG Technical Advisor) to join our team in Gothenburg, Sweden.

The position
Envirotainer was founded in 1985 and currently has a fleet of more than 6,000 active airfreight containers that ensure that temperature-sensitive pharmaceuticals can be delivered from where they are produced to the patient safely. Every day, millions of doses of pharmaceuticals from all types of pharmaceutical manufacturers worldwide are successfully shipped in their containers. Due to continued strong growth, we are now looking for a BI & Data Analytics Manager to join the Envirotainer IT Architecture & Data Analytics team.
Your primary focus will be to manage the BI & Data Analytics domain from an IT perspective. This includes managing and developing new and existing data platforms and tools that provides the business with data, tools, and capabilities to analyze data and produce business reports, dashboards, and analytical insights needed for data driven decisions and formal reporting.

Life at Winningtemp

Winningtemp offers the market an unique and revolutionary technology for creating successful work places. This is done by collecting and visualizing real-time data that describes the employee's experience of leadership, meaningfulness, control and joy at work.
Today, Winningtemp consists of a wonderful and ambitious group of 115+ people in the offices in Gothenburg, Stockholm, Oslo and London. The head quarter is newly renovated (of course with a lot of purple ) in the middle of central Gothenburg.

At Winningtemp we care about the well-being of our employees and therefore we of course work continuously with our own tool to be an attractive employer. We have grown by over 2100% in recent years and we continue to grow.
By 2024, our goal is to make an impact on more than 4 million people through our product.

So what is the role about?

As a Data Engineer at Winningtemp, you will work with many different internal stake holders, with a focus on maintaining data, creating data tools and improving internal processes within your area.
Your mission is to ensure that our data generates actionable and valuable results for the business, and ultimately our customers. You will have an important role linked to an important mission of ours; to become One Winningtemp throughout the whole organization.

Other areas of responsibilities;

Your team and manager ‍ ‍ ‍

In this role you will work close to our senior Data scientist, Miroslav, someone you will have daily communication with. Miroslav has two PhDs, including one in artificial intelligence from Stockholm University. He has eight years of experience in academia - during which his research was funded by some of the most prestigious fellowships available, including the Marie-Sklodowska Currie Fellowship. Miroslav works in Stockholm, but this position is also available in Gothenburg.

Miroslav is a very appreciated colleague, dedicated and eager to share his knowledge and experience in the field, everything to make you learn as much as possible.
In this role, you will also be working close to all our different departments, meaning you will have collaboration over the whole organization.

You will be reporting to our CFO and be a part of his team. The CFO is situated in Gothenburg.

Are you the one we are looking for?

Winningtemp is the place where we all succeed together, something that you also feel is essential in your daily work, teamwork makes the dreamwork. You are therefor a team player and enjoy sharing ideas and learnings with the people around you.

You appreciate to plan your work well, and always complete what you've started. You set high goals for yourself, and always does what it takes to achieve good results. In addition to that, you look outside the box to think in new ways, meaning you are good at finding solutions to problems that arise. You are up-to-date in your area of expertise, and you have a great interest in always learning more about new techniques and systems within your area.

You have 4+ years of experience in a Data Engineer role, and you have a degree, or its equivalent, in Computer Science, Statistics, Informatics, Information Systemor similar. You haveadvanced SQL knowledge and experience working with relational databases, query authoring (SQL) as well as working familiarity with a variety of databases. You have beenbuilding and optimizing ‘big data’ data pipelines, architectures, and data sets. You have been working with structured and unstructured datasets, and you are used to build processes supporting data transformation, data structures, metadata, dependency, and workload management. You have successfully manipulated, processed, and extracted value from large disconnected datasets.

You have experience in using one and/or several following software and tools:


No worries if you do not experience in all of the areas and/or tools, we will guide you along the way!

What's in it for me?

Why Winningtemp?

As an employee at Winningtemp, you will be part of our purple family

With us, you will find energetic and loyal colleagues who help each other succeed together. With us, everyone is equally valuable, regardless of gender, ethnicity and background. Diversity is also something we work actively with and something we value. We share happiness every day, not only for our product and the work we do, but also for each other. The commitment of each employee is what really makes us stand out from other companies. You can expect a supportive workplace where everyone works together towards our vision; to forever change how people succeed together!

We promise you; you will be impressed!

Our recruitment process includes;

Personality and logical test - > Interview with recruiter - > Interview with the future manager - > Interview with closest colleague - > Reference check - > Offer

We handle applications continuously so don't hesitate to apply as soon as possible!

Coody is changing the consulting industry with a new model designed to benefit the individual, not the consulting company. We do this by combining the benefits of being a freelancer with the security of a traditional employment.

This means that we pay the best salary in the industry, provide fantastic benefits while at the same time being a secure workplace with a fixed monthly salary, stable employment terms and above all - a wonderful community and really good exchange of knowledge.

Why chose when you can have both?

We have simply stripped away all unnecessary overhead between yourself and the company to be able to offer you a platform that will help you achieve your priorities in life and at the same time work on meaningful projects for some of the country's most exciting digital leaders.

(We do work for companies such as Spotify, Mathem, Hemnet, Bokio, Polestar, Tobii and others).

WE ARE HIRING DATA ENGINEERS TO BE PART OF CHANGING THE WORLD OF CONSULTING TOGETHER WITH COODY AND OUR CLIENTS!

What we look for

We are looking for data engineer to work together with our exciting clients who are leading products companies, startups and scaleups. You’ll work as an integral part of our clients team to solve complex technical challenges in modern cloud environments.

In addition to this, you are interested in handling larger amounts of data and have worked as a Data Engineer or a similar role before where development has been in focus. When working as a consultant with Coody it’s crucial that you are communicative and can work well with others.

Your background

What we offer

We offer you an opportunity to work with exciting challenges and projects in modern cloud environments where you will work with developers and data scientists.

At your service is an experienced sales-team with best-in-industry tools and the right network to find you the perfect assignment and give you the best time of your career!

You will focus on working on longer assignments for between 6 months to 3 years, that will both challenge your knowledge and give you the best possible use of your skill set. You will work as an integral part of the client’s organization, remote or on-site. We do not work with customers in morally dubious industries.

We have a limit on quarterly hires - so don’t wait. Send us your application and get in contact with us in a blink of an eye!

In a world where product size labels are unreliable, Volumental is the footwear industry's leading FitTech™ company, using 3D scans and a one-of-a-kind, AI-powered recommendation engine to match everyone with the shoes that fit them best.

With top brand and retail partners across the world including New Balance, Bauer, The Athlete's Foot, Ecco and XXL, our footprint spans 2500+ stores across 46 countries, and counting.

Volumental’s data and machine learning platforms power all our products, communicate with 3000+ devices spread across six continents, and serve 18 million users - quickly growing. This brings in a large variation of data modalities including, 10s of millions of 3D scans, purchases, inventory, product catalog data, user interactions, and many more. To make this data useful and easy to work with, it is organized, indexed, and served in the different formats that satisfy the needs of our different products that build on top of it.

We are now looking for a data engineer to help us expand our analytics products - ensuring they have access to all the multi-modal data they require to provide an engaging, reliable, and fast experience.

Description:
Take the opportunity to join the exciting change journey Electromobility is embarking, when creating the future electric powertrains for our customers as well as the future working place to nurture innovation. Electromobility is one of the main development areas within Volvo Group Truck and was created to be in the forefront of electrified transport solutions for a more sustainable tomorrow.
Are you a System engineer with an analytic mindset and a passion for working with quality in the state-of-the art battery development area? Join us now!

This is us, your new colleagues at Electromobility
We are responsible for the transition from conventional powertrains to electromobility and to secure a stepwise implementation in different segments/regions. We develop and drive the electromobility product portfolio for Trucks and Buses as well as creating opportunities for all business areas within Volvo Group. Electromobility is a growing agile driven organization in place to shape the future!
The importance of electromobility is growing every day and a key component within the electrified powertrain is the Energy Storage System (ESS). We are accountable for the lifecycle management of the Energy Storage System, from advanced engineering, throughout product development into the maintenance phase.
You will be part of an agile and approachable organization with skilled product teams consisting of passionate people. We work in an optimistic atmosphere, where joy, knowledge sharing, and openness are key characteristics, working with tasks you cannot imagine today.


You will be part of the Product management team for Medium Range Energy Storage Systems as part of the product development area. We are expanding and are recruiting a System engineer with a customer-centric approach responsible for product and field quality. You will have an important role for the quality of the products and understanding how the battery systems are applied by our customers. You will be involved in technical decisions towards projects and suppliers, making sure that we continuously improve the quality.


We believe that to be successful in this position, you will have the System engineering view on quality for trucks that are in production and aftermarket, always with the customer in focus. You need a good understanding of the applications and how the battery packs are used and applied. You have an analytic- mindset and putting pride in delivering high quality products and solutions. Confident in leading system solution towards suppliers and product teams. We also believe that you feel comfortable of owning and taking responsibility of your system and quality and do so with great attitude.

About Validio

Validio is the next generation data quality and reliability company. Our next generation data quality platform monitors and validates both data in motion and data at rest across organizations data pipelines. Validio’s mission is to eliminate bad data and enable organizations to be data-driven with confidence. From startups to multi-billion dollar unicorns, Validio is used by data leaders of all sizes. We believe that you shouldn’t have to be an AirBnB, Uber or Netflix in order to have advanced ML-based data quality technology in place. We also believe that modern data teams and data engineers get better ROI by spending their time on other business-critical tasks rather than building and maintaining their own data quality infrastructure.

Here you will work with a senior team of data and engineering professionals with backgrounds from renowned research institutions, leading startups, and established tech companies. Named as one of the hottest start-ups in Stockholm by publications such as Wired, we are gearing up for expansion, and now you can be part of our journey!

About the role

Validio is on an exciting growth journey and this is a rare opportunity to be a founding team member and leader of the Customer Success team in a very purpose-driven organization. This is a great opportunity to help shape the future of the data industry and its real-world impact.

Validio is looking for someone to build and lead our Customer Success function from the ground up, meaning ownership of customer satisfaction and success, as well increasing the product adoption among existing customers. At Validio we work on some of the most exciting modern data infrastructure architectures and our customers challenge us with interesting new data quality validation and monitoring requirements continuously. As the complexity grows for both us and our customers, we are looking to our Customer Success Lead to strategize and lead customers to solutions. This is done with clear data requirement mapping, use case discovery, Validio evangelism, and oftentimes educating users about our product.

As our Customer Success Lead, you will manage our customer relationships, become a trusted advisor to our users, and contribute to Validio’s fast-growing success. You will be the voice of the user and collaborate closely with product and engineering to make sure key improvements are added to the roadmap. You must be able to capture and contextualize product feedback for our engineering and product teams, track issue resolutions, explain new feature enhancements, and mitigate/prioritize any pain points before they become critical issues.

Life at Winningtemp

Winningtemp offers the market an unique and revolutionary technology for creating successful work places. This is done by collecting and visualizing real-time data that describes the employee's experience of leadership, meaningfulness, control and joy at work.
Today, Winningtemp consists of a wonderful and ambitious group of 115+ people in the offices in Gothenburg, Stockholm, Oslo and London. The head quarter is newly renovated (of course with a lot of purple ) in the middle of central Gothenburg.

At Winningtemp we care about the well-being of our employees and therefore we of course work continuously with our own tool to be an attractive employer. We have grown by over 2100% in recent years and we continue to grow.
By 2024, our goal is to make an impact on more than 4 million people through our product.

So what is the role about?

As a Data Engineer at Winningtemp, you will work with many different internal stake holders, with a focus on maintaining data, creating data tools and improving internal processes within your area.
Your mission is to ensure that our data generates actionable and valuable results for the business, and ultimately our customers. You will have an important role linked to an important mission of ours; to become One Winningtemp throughout the whole organization.

Other areas of responsibilities;

Your team and manager ‍ ‍ ‍

In this role you will work close to our senior Data scientist, Miroslav, someone you will have daily communication with. Miroslav has two PhDs, including one in artificial intelligence from Stockholm University. He has eight years of experience in academia - during which his research was funded by some of the most prestigious fellowships available, including the Marie-Sklodowska Currie Fellowship. Miroslav works in Stockholm, but this position is also available in Gothenburg.

Miroslav is a very appreciated colleague, dedicated and eager to share his knowledge and experience in the field, everything to make you learn as much as possible.
In this role, you will also be working close to all our different departments, meaning you will have collaboration over the whole organization.

You will be reporting to our CFO and be a part of his team. The CFO is situated in Gothenburg.

Are you the one we are looking for?

Winningtemp is the place where we all succeed together, something that you also feel is essential in your daily work, teamwork makes the dreamwork. You are therefor a team player and enjoy sharing ideas and learnings with the people around you.

You appreciate to plan your work well, and always complete what you've started. You set high goals for yourself, and always does what it takes to achieve good results. In addition to that, you look outside the box to think in new ways, meaning you are good at finding solutions to problems that arise. You are up-to-date in your area of expertise, and you have a great interest in always learning more about new techniques and systems within your area.

You have 4+ years of experience in a Data Engineer role, and you have a degree, or its equivalent, in Computer Science, Statistics, Informatics, Information Systemor similar. You haveadvanced SQL knowledge and experience working with relational databases, query authoring (SQL) as well as working familiarity with a variety of databases. You have beenbuilding and optimizing ‘big data’ data pipelines, architectures, and data sets. You have been working with structured and unstructured datasets, and you are used to build processes supporting data transformation, data structures, metadata, dependency, and workload management. You have successfully manipulated, processed, and extracted value from large disconnected datasets.

You have experience in using one and/or several following software and tools:


No worries if you do not experience in all of the areas and/or tools, we will guide you along the way!

What's in it for me?

Why Winningtemp?

As an employee at Winningtemp, you will be part of our purple family

With us, you will find energetic and loyal colleagues who help each other succeed together. With us, everyone is equally valuable, regardless of gender, ethnicity and background. Diversity is also something we work actively with and something we value. We share happiness every day, not only for our product and the work we do, but also for each other. The commitment of each employee is what really makes us stand out from other companies. You can expect a supportive workplace where everyone works together towards our vision; to forever change how people succeed together!

We promise you; you will be impressed!

Our recruitment process includes;

Personality and logical test - > Interview with recruiter - > Interview with the future manager - > Interview with closest colleague - > Reference check - > Offer

We handle applications continuously so don't hesitate to apply as soon as possible!

Description:
Coody is changing the consulting industry with a new model designed to benefit the individual, not the consulting company. We do this by combining the benefits of being a freelancer with the security of a traditional employment.

This means that we pay the best salary in the industry, provide fantastic benefits while at the same time being a secure workplace with a fixed monthly salary, stable employment terms and above all - a wonderful community and really good exchange of knowledge.

Why chose when you can have both?

We have simply stripped away all unnecessary overhead between yourself and the company to be able to offer you a platform that will help you achieve your priorities in life and at the same time work on meaningful projects for some of the country's most exciting digital leaders.

(We do work for companies such as Spotify, Mathem, Hemnet, Bokio, Polestar, Tobii and others).

WE ARE HIRING DATA ENGINEERS TO BE PART OF CHANGING THE WORLD OF CONSULTING TOGETHER WITH COODY AND OUR CLIENTS!

What we look for

We are looking for data engineer to work together with our exciting clients who are leading products companies, startups and scaleups. You’ll work as an integral part of our clients team to solve complex technical challenges in modern cloud environments.

In addition to this, you are interested in handling larger amounts of data and have worked as a Data Engineer or a similar role before where development has been in focus. When working as a consultant with Coody it’s crucial that you are communicative and can work well with others.

Your background

What we offer

We offer you an opportunity to work with exciting challenges and projects in modern cloud environments where you will work with developers and data scientists.

At your service is an experienced sales-team with best-in-industry tools and the right network to find you the perfect assignment and give you the best time of your career!

You will focus on working on longer assignments for between 6 months to 3 years, that will both challenge your knowledge and give you the best possible use of your skill set. You will work as an integral part of the client’s organization, remote or on-site. We do not work with customers in morally dubious industries.

We have a limit on quarterly hires - so don’t wait. Send us your application and get in contact with us in a blink of an eye!

In a world where product size labels are unreliable, Volumental is the footwear industry's leading FitTech™ company, using 3D scans and a one-of-a-kind, AI-powered recommendation engine to match everyone with the shoes that fit them best.

With top brand and retail partners across the world including New Balance, Bauer, The Athlete's Foot, Ecco and XXL, our footprint spans 2500+ stores across 46 countries, and counting.

Volumental’s data and machine learning platforms power all our products, communicate with 3000+ devices spread across six continents, and serve 18 million users - quickly growing. This brings in a large variation of data modalities including, 10s of millions of 3D scans, purchases, inventory, product catalog data, user interactions, and many more. To make this data useful and easy to work with, it is organized, indexed, and served in the different formats that satisfy the needs of our different products that build on top of it.

We are now looking for a data engineer to help us expand our analytics products - ensuring they have access to all the multi-modal data they require to provide an engaging, reliable, and fast experience.

THE ROLE

WHAT YOU WILL DO

THE TEAM

Job_title: System Engineer within Energy Storage System at Electromobility
Description:
Take the opportunity to join the exciting change journey Electromobility is embarking, when creating the future electric powertrains for our customers as well as the future working place to nurture innovation. Electromobility is one of the main development areas within Volvo Group Truck and was created to be in the forefront of electrified transport solutions for a more sustainable tomorrow.
Are you a System engineer with an analytic mindset and a passion for working with quality in the state-of-the art battery development area? Join us now!

This is us, your new colleagues at Electromobility
We are responsible for the transition from conventional powertrains to electromobility and to secure a stepwise implementation in different segments/regions. We develop and drive the electromobility product portfolio for Trucks and Buses as well as creating opportunities for all business areas within Volvo Group. Electromobility is a growing agile driven organization in place to shape the future!
The importance of electromobility is growing every day and a key component within the electrified powertrain is the Energy Storage System (ESS). We are accountable for the lifecycle management of the Energy Storage System, from advanced engineering, throughout product development into the maintenance phase.
You will be part of an agile and approachable organization with skilled product teams consisting of passionate people. We work in an optimistic atmosphere, where joy, knowledge sharing, and openness are key characteristics, working with tasks you cannot imagine today.


You will be part of the Product management team for Medium Range Energy Storage Systems as part of the product development area. We are expanding and are recruiting a System engineer with a customer-centric approach responsible for product and field quality. You will have an important role for the quality of the products and understanding how the battery systems are applied by our customers. You will be involved in technical decisions towards projects and suppliers, making sure that we continuously improve the quality.


We believe that to be successful in this position, you will have the System engineering view on quality for trucks that are in production and aftermarket, always with the customer in focus. You need a good understanding of the applications and how the battery packs are used and applied. You have an analytic- mindset and putting pride in delivering high quality products and solutions. Confident in leading system solution towards suppliers and product teams. We also believe that you feel comfortable of owning and taking responsibility of your system and quality and do so with great attitude.

ABOUT NORMATIVE
Any company would say its employees are smart, capable, and fun to work with – and our employees certainly are! But we’re also driven by an unshakable sense of purpose, an urgency to act, and the motivation to devote our talents and energy to fighting the planet’s most important fight.

You will be working closely with engineers across several teams, collaborating with DevOps and engineering management in ensuring teams have effective tools, frameworks and processes to help them deliver the right level of quality, at the right time, with confidence.

Description:
About this role

At Ingrid, we believe that Customer Success begins with incredible people. If you have strong technical background, experience in customer success, and looking to join a startup with global potential, then read on!

Ingrid is currently looking for a customer-focused, highly technical Customer Experience Engineer to join our growing Customer Success team! We are looking for someone who can fill the role of a technical person that helps our customers, but also understands the engineering side. Someone who helps customers get past any technical hurdles in the pre-sales and post-sales stages. Someone who acts as the bridge between Engineering and Ingrid's customers.

Our ideal Customer Experience Engineer will always put the customer first, seeking to understand what the customer needs to accomplish — whether it's solving a technical problem or filling a feature request. We are looking for creative, critical thinking individuals with a tenacious love for problem solving.

If you are looking for an opportunity to couple technical knowledge and customer success, this job is perfect for you. If you are thinking “I love to code, but I really want to be doing more than just that. I like people, and I want to help people" then this job is definitely perfect for you!

Our Customer Success team is on a mission to become one of the best teams in SaaS and our team consists of Customer Experience Engineers and Customer Success Managers. We believe in empathy, in transparency, in building trust with our customers, and in establishing long-term relationships by focusing on our customers’ goals and needs. Ingrid’s wins are tied to our customer’s wins.

Ingrid is a highly technical platform, but we do not expect you to have full-time engineer work experience in the past. You should have some understanding of technical concepts, a little coding experience to feel comfortable in your communication with customers and we will teach you the rest you need to be successful at Ingrid.

At Eppow, we’re passionate about solving complex engineering problems which have actual societal value.

What does that mean? These past years the focus has been the patient journey which is great but one very vital aspect has been forgotten. What about the doctors and nurses? We all expect to meet a doctor or a nurse at a hospital, not an empty chair. Here is where Eppow comes in - we empower hospitals, clinics and healthcare professionals to find, contact and contract each other unrestrictedly.

We are a diverse and growing team with our headquarters in Norrsken House, Stockholm. Together we are leading the development of the healthcare industry and are now looking for a savvy developer that wants to help us evolve the platform.

ABOUT TECH AT EPPOW
As a Software Engineer you will be a vital part of our tech team, meaning you will have the mandate and influence over how we develop the platform and structure our tech stack. As we grow into our costume, we now need to re-envision our core architecture. Some of the underlying questions that are driving this change are:

ABOUT THE ROLE

You like to be given much freedom and appreciate having the responsibility that comes with that. You are not afraid to develop new solutions, and you think it's educational to fail. Do you want to be a part of revolutionizing the healthcare industry and be a part of the solution? Join as our Dev team and help us evolve our platform and let’s have fun whilst doing it!

About Validio

Validio is the next generation data quality and reliability company. Our next generation data quality platform monitors and validates both data in motion and data at rest across organizations data pipelines. Validio’s mission is to eliminate bad data and enable organizations to be data-driven with confidence. From startups to multi-billion dollar unicorns, Validio is used by data leaders of all sizes. We believe that you shouldn’t have to be an AirBnB, Uber or Netflix in order to have advanced ML-based data quality technology in place. We also believe that modern data teams and data engineers get better ROI by spending their time on other business-critical tasks rather than building and maintaining their own data quality infrastructure.

Here you will work with a senior team of data and engineering professionals with backgrounds from renowned research institutions, leading startups, and established tech companies. Named as one of the hottest start-ups in Stockholm by publications such as Wired, we are gearing up for expansion, and now you can be part of our journey!

About the role

Validio is on an exciting growth journey and this is a rare opportunity to be a founding team member and leader of the Customer Success team in a very purpose-driven organization. This is a great opportunity to help shape the future of the data industry and its real-world impact.

Validio is looking for someone to build and lead our Customer Success function from the ground up, meaning ownership of customer satisfaction and success, as well increasing the product adoption among existing customers. At Validio we work on some of the most exciting modern data infrastructure architectures and our customers challenge us with interesting new data quality validation and monitoring requirements continuously. As the complexity grows for both us and our customers, we are looking to our Customer Success Lead to strategize and lead customers to solutions. This is done with clear data requirement mapping, use case discovery, Validio evangelism, and oftentimes educating users about our product.

As our Customer Success Lead, you will manage our customer relationships, become a trusted advisor to our users, and contribute to Validio’s fast-growing success. You will be the voice of the user and collaborate closely with product and engineering to make sure key improvements are added to the roadmap. You must be able to capture and contextualize product feedback for our engineering and product teams, track issue resolutions, explain new feature enhancements, and mitigate/prioritize any pain points before they become critical issues.

Description:
About the role
You’ll be part of an agile autonomous team working on extending and refining our core systems. Our teams solve a wide array of complex problems, below are some examples.

Capacity management - We believe in quick, exact, and efficient delivery. To know when we can deliver a specific parcel, or how to maximize locker compartment utilization, we continuously adapt and gain knowledge about of the current parcel delivery capacity in our locker network and how it changes over time. We use machine learning to model consumer pick-up behavior and forecast future parcel volumes from merchants.

Driver route optimization - Driving is at the core of what we do. Well-planned routes are essential for driver happiness, consumer satisfaction, and our ability to offer sustainable deliveries.

Locker fleet management - Our lockers are equipped with a tailor-made computer, a 4G modem with an intuitive interface. With a large growing fleet of lockers in multiple countries, we solve problems such as performing safe and secure software roll-outs, inventory management, and detection of malfunctioning hardware.

About you
We’re hiring for multiple teams and we are looking for both senior engineers or you with a couple of years of experience looking for your next move - If you are a skilled problem solver who loves coding and making complex things work, then this is the place for you! At Budbee we value individuals who are keen to learn, and your eagerness to develop your skill set will probably be your strongest asset when joining us. Beyond that we imagine that you have the following:

In order for you to thrive at Budbee, you need to like the fast-paced environment and not be afraid to get shit under your fingernails. Let's be honest, we are in an incredibly exciting phase where much is uncertain and not decided. In this business, you need to have thick skin to get by, like changes and not be afraid to set new structures, set processes, and create new WoW.

Diversity and inclusion are very important for us, and we also know that we don’t know everything. So if your passion is problem-solving, and coding and you have a strong willingness to learn, but don’t tick all the boxes above – don't hesitate to apply no matter who you are and let us know how you can contribute to our journey.

This recruitment process consists of personality tests via Alva Labs and background checks via Verifiera as a review of previous public criminal records. The result is public information that is handled confidentially. This is mandatory for all recruitment processes at Budbee in Sweden.

Job_title: Backend engineer with a love for gaming
Description:
Abios Gaming continues to grow and now we are searching for experienced engineers to join their gaming-loving team at their amazing office near Torsplan! Are you a backend engineer who wants to be a part of an exciting growth journey ahead at a company with a unique product that values its employees high? Apply today, we apply continuous selection!
About the role
Abios is a Stockholm-based esports data provider, founded in 2013. We distribute industry-leading esports data and technology across the globe. Our customers include world-famous esports teams, search engines, and sportsbooks. We provide our customers with data APIs, data visualisation iframes and odds on top of which they can build the next generation of esports products.
